This paper discusses meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning concerned with learning to learn. The paper specifically focuses on the comparison between recurrent models and deep representations with gradient descent for meta-learning. Given this focus, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also includes experiments on image classification, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
